10:28.475 --> 10:48.575
people and keep them and but that we will jointly 
determine through a series of area research

10:28.475 --> 10:48.575
committees. There are four of them in the 
department has that we work with those area

10:53.785 --> 11:05.400
committees in areas or areas of materials and 
pavements and structures and economics and

10:53.785 --> 11:05.400
planning. We work with those to develop the 
research program for the coming year. And we have a

11:10.046 --> 11:15.774
strong input into what sorts of research is going 
to be done. So we and the University of Texas, and

11:16.975 --> 11:23.083
they operate the same way now, do the research for 
the Texas Highway Department, for the State

11:24.430 --> 11:29.616
Department of Highways and Public 
Transportation in the state. Now, in addition, we

11:30.757 --> 11:43.932
do, of course, this year, for example, that'll be 
about $1.6 million that we will do in our

11:30.757 --> 11:43.932
cooperative research program with the Highway 
Department. But now, in addition, for the last 10

11:44.632 --> 11:49.678
or 15 years, We do direct contract work with the 
federal government, with other states, with

11:51.768 --> 12:03.346
other state agencies, with trade associations, 
and with private industry. So the co-op program,

12:04.048 --> 12:18.771
the program of the highway department, which 
originally was our total program, now this year

12:04.048 --> 12:18.771
we'll have about, the year we're in now, about $7.2 
million worth of research, of which the states

12:19.561 --> 12:26.812
will be about in our cooperative about 1.6. So it's 
a very, very important part of our research

12:27.233 --> 12:42.195
activity, in that it is the one program which we 
